The air conditioner compressor lies at the heart of your BMW's climate control system. It works by compressing a gas refrigerant into a liquid and lowering the temperature of the refrigerant below freezing. This liquid refrigerant is then injected into the evaporator core inside the passenger compartment, where the blower motor cools the air before it exits the AC vents.
